title: Grateful Dead Live at Soldiers' and Sailors' Memorial Hall on 1979-12-11
lineage: SBD > Cassette Master > Cassette > DAT (44.1k) > Sony R500 > Behringer UltraMatch SRC2000 > SEK'D Prodif plus > Samplitude v7.02 Professional > FLAC16
description: Jack Straw, Loser, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, Easy To Love You, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Terrapin Station-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E:Alabama Getaway-> E: Promised Land

reviews.review_text:
Tight and standard Stanley Theater '79 is my standard for China>Rider. Just listened to this one. Phil is on and in charge. --Nice like.. Started with ETLU, I figure if that's good by the 6th song, show is worth a listen. SHaKeDown> Samson was as advertised. Jerry super stylie slide on, rippin' the high's. Brent and Phil right in there with the with the funk a' munch stuff.* Terrapin is in prime "pre-studio form". Hey I'd say.. Let's record it, and lets add a horn and string section. Lost sailor... it's all text book.  Great stuff.. Classic quality. Lick, stick, and RoCk/// Need to amend.. NFA Intro.. Hello?  And T adds, after listen to fist 4 songs, It's all about the Abilene in Loser. If Jer hits that note .. You're in!

awesome Show is tight, sound is great, we've got ourselves a winner here.

Three cheers for CM! This is one of those shows that is great from opening notes to encore. Enjoy!

FYI, this is the better of the two Charlie Miller sources. The other has an AUD patch in Jack Straw. This was upgraded to a SBD patch in Jack Straw.

This is a good one, right here. The sound is tight and wonderful here--no sloppy jams, only wonder being born from every single note. But the real magic starts around Althea and doesn't leave. The Ship of Fools is wonderful and the Terrapin is crisp and totally perfect, but it's the intro to NFA that really blew me away. Woah. What a good one, folks. Give it a listen. You won't regret it.

Brent has found his way .... Too bad all of the shows from here dont sound that great cause this show is smoking! The energy is fantastic and Brent is fitting in quite nicely. Give this CM sbd a listen now!

Can’t pass up The GD only played this Estimated Jam this one time. Please stop by and take a close listen. Mere days from the 80s this second set harkens of the last 1000 days of music rather than portend the future 1000 days.
